.TH BUSYBOX-STATIC 1 "2026-05-06" "InterGenOS" "InterGenOS Manual"
.SH NAME
busybox.static \- statically-linked busybox userland for early-boot environments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B /usr/bin/busybox.static
.RI [ APPLET ]
.RI [ ARGS ]
.PP
.B /usr/bin/busybox.static
.B --help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B busybox.static
is a statically-linked build of busybox 1.37.0, intended for initramfs
environments where no other userland or shared libraries are available.

This is the static variant; it embeds the C library and so runs before
any filesystem mount or library resolver is in place. Each invocation
behaves as a different applet depending on the first argument or the
basename used to invoke it (busybox dispatches by argv[0]).

.B busybox-static
is consumed by InterGenOS's live-boot initramfs (built by
.IR installer/init/build-initramfs.sh ).
The custom
.IR /init
script (at
.IR installer/init/init.sh )
exec's a small set of applets:
.B sh, mount, umount, switch_root, awk, blkid, sleep, modprobe, mkdir,
.B cp, ln, echo, cat, printf, grep, sed, find.

For a normal interactive busybox userland on the running system, use the
regular dynamic-linked
.B busybox
package instead (when authored). Mixing the two is intentional: the
static variant is for initramfs only; the dynamic variant is for shells
and scripts.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --help
Show all available applets.
.TP
.B --list
List applet names, one per line.
.TP
.BR APPLET " [\fIARGS\fP...]"
Invoke
.IR APPLET
(e.g.,
.BR sh ,
.BR mount )
with the remaining arguments. Same effect as creating a symlink named
.IR APPLET
pointing at busybox.static and invoking it.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/busybox.static
The statically-linked binary.
.TP
.I /usr/share/man/man1/busybox-static.1
This page.
.SH RATIONALE
The
.B .static
suffix is deliberate: it preserves the
.IR /usr/bin/busybox
namespace for a future dynamic-linked busybox package, makes the
distinction visible to anyone inspecting the filesystem, and matches the
naming used by
.IR installer/init/build-initramfs.sh .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR busybox (1)
on the upstream busybox documentation,
.BR initramfs (8),
.IR installer/init/init.sh
(InterGenOS live-boot dispatcher).
